SIMPLE: mimicry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mimicry
<hw>Mim"ic*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or practice of one who mimics; ludicrous imitation for sport or
ridicule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Protective resemblance; the
resemblance which certain animals and plants exhibit to other animals
and plants or to the natural objects among which they live, -- a
characteristic which serves as their chief means of protection against
enemies; imitation; mimesis; mimetism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mimir</ent>⟦br⟧
